    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/flags.css">
    <div class="subheading">
      <div class="heading-text">
        <h1>Site render flags</h1>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-content">
        <p>
          Here you can configure how the site is served by setting cookies:
        </p>
        <form action="./" class="flags-form">
          <label>
            <div class="input-container">
              <input type="checkbox" name="client-render" value="1"{{#if flags.client-render}} checked{{/if}}>
            </div>
            <div class="desc">
              <div class="main">Prevent serverside rendering of articles.</div>
              <div class="sub">Article fetching &amp; rendering will be handled by JS.</div>
            </div>
          </label>
          <label>
            <div class="input-container">
              <input type="checkbox" name="avoid-wikipedia" value="1"{{#if flags.avoid-wikipedia}} checked{{/if}}>
            </div>
            <div class="desc">
              <div class="main">Avoid going to wikipedia for article data.</div>
              <div class="sub">Although all articles will be about Hulk Hogan. But who <em>doesn't</em> want that?</div>
            </div>
          </label>
          <label>
            <div class="input-container">
              <input type="checkbox" name="prevent-sw" value="1"{{#if flags.prevent-sw}} checked{{/if}}>
            </div>
            <div class="desc">
              <div class="main">Prevent ServiceWorker registration.</div>
              <div class="sub">Will also unregister an existing ServiceWorker. This removes all offline-first behaviour.</div>
            </div>
          </label>
          <label>
            <div class="input-container">
              <input type="checkbox" name="no-css-async-hack" value="1"{{#if flags.no-css-async-hack}} checked{{/if}}>
            </div>
            <div class="desc">
              <div class="main">Don't load CSS with XHR.</div>
              <div class="sub">This is done as a hack around Chrome/Safari's blocking behaviour.</div>
            </div>
          </label>
          <div class="submit-container">
            <button type="submit" class="material-button">Save</button>
          </div>
        </form>
        <p>
          Or use the following querystring to overwrite flags for a single
          request:
        </p>
        <div class="flags-query">?use-url-flags&</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>